<div id="review_2338225166" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2338225166" />
    <a title="Matthew Ted" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/57003346-matthew-ted"><img alt="Matthew Ted" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1578773686p2/57003346.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2338225166?book_show_action=true">Apr 15, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Matthew Ted" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Matthew Ted" href="/user/show/57003346-matthew-ted">Matthew Ted</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780547572291" href="/book/show/12346742-ubik">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/57003346-matthew-ted?shelf=20th-century">20th-century</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/57003346-matthew-ted?shelf=read-2020">read-2020</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/57003346-matthew-ted?shelf=science-fiction">science-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/57003346-matthew-ted?shelf=lit-american">lit-american</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2338225166" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5084272059987752279">59th book of 2020. <br/><br/><img src='https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1588182562i/29377618._SX540_.jpg' width='700' height='200' alt='description' class='gr-hostedUserImg'/><br/><br/>I&apos;m going to carefully say I love <i>Philip K.</i> Dick. I&apos;ll say the writing isn&apos;t phenomenal, it&apos;s very cinematic, which I usually don&apos;t care for. Books excite me when they make me think, or they linger in my head, and Dick manages to do that, without the fancy writing. Though, I do like fancy language. I like the word fancy too. <br/><br/>This book, as expected, is a little mind-blowing. Returning to his wonderful, favourite theme: Reality. And moreover, what is reality? I can&apos;t say much wi</span>
  <span id="freeText5084272059987752279" style="display:none">59th book of 2020. <br><br><img src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1588182562i/29377618._SX540_.jpg" width="700" height="200" alt="description" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br><br>I'm going to carefully say I love <i>Philip K.</i> Dick. I'll say the writing isn't phenomenal, it's very cinematic, which I usually don't care for. Books excite me when they make me think, or they linger in my head, and Dick manages to do that, without the fancy writing. Though, I do like fancy language. I like the word fancy too. <br><br>This book, as expected, is a little mind-blowing. Returning to his wonderful, favourite theme: Reality. And moreover, what is reality? I can't say much without spoiling the many twist and turns this book takes you through, which also I means I can't scream out the excitement, confusion and (slight) fear, on finishing. The best way to sum it up is by using someone else's quote, Grossman's: <br><br><i>"a deeply unsettling existential horror story, a nightmare you'll never be sure you've woken up from"</i><br><br>Exactly how it feels. Fans of <i>The Crying of Lot 49</i> and the movie <i>Inception</i>, converge here. I'll wait for you to arrive, whilst pondering my own existence, and or, reality.</span>
  <a data-text-id="5084272059987752279" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


