    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_2320079108" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2320079108" />
    <a title="Robin (Bridge Four)" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/14105531-robin-bridge-four"><img alt="Robin (Bridge Four)" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1473392517p2/14105531.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2320079108?book_show_action=true">Mar 15, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Robin (Bridge Four)" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Robin (Bridge Four)" href="/user/show/14105531-robin-bridge-four">Robin (Bridge Four)</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/14105531-robin-bridge-four?shelf=2018-reads">2018-reads</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/14105531-robin-bridge-four?shelf=buddy-read">buddy-read</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/14105531-robin-bridge-four?shelf=bb-b-2018">bb-b-2018</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/14105531-robin-bridge-four?shelf=sci-fi">sci-fi</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2320079108" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13169047619734803775"><b>2.5 Half-Life Stars</b><br/><br/><b>Buddy Read with <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/user/show/8192509-gavin' rel='nofollow noopener'>Gavin the Great</a> at <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/group/show/148164-buddies-books-and-baubles' rel='nofollow noopener'>BB&amp;B</a></b><br/><br/><b>Ubik is a wonder, it is anything and everything you could ever need.</b> It can taste like fresh brewed coffee, or a nice hoppy beer, or be used as salad dressing. It can relieve a headache or stomach ache or clean household items. It slices and It dices with a never dulling edge, plus makes your hair shine like never before. It will help you sleep, stops perspiration, freshens breath and will uplift your breasts. <b>But wait there’s more…..</b><br/><br/>It i</span>
  <span id="freeText13169047619734803775" style="display:none"><b>2.5 Half-Life Stars</b><br /><br /><b>Buddy Read with <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/show/8192509-gavin" rel="nofollow noopener">Gavin the Great</a> at <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/group/show/148164-buddies-books-and-baubles" rel="nofollow noopener">BB&amp;B</a></b><br /><br /><b>Ubik is a wonder, it is anything and everything you could ever need.</b> It can taste like fresh brewed coffee, or a nice hoppy beer, or be used as salad dressing. It can relieve a headache or stomach ache or clean household items. It slices and It dices with a never dulling edge, plus makes your hair shine like never before. It will help you sleep, stops perspiration, freshens breath and will uplift your breasts. <b>But wait there’s more…..</b><br /><br />It is hard to read a Sci-Fi book from 1969 and not feel like it is dated especially since the far off future is 1992. Philip K. Dick (PKD) thought we’d make it a lot farther than we actually did technology wise with the flying cars and talking electronics but since 1992 is our past sometimes it is hard to get past the things that are so off for that time period.<br /><br />A few things that are pretty cool in this book is the actual world and some of the discoveries in it. Like when your loved one dies you don’t bury them anymore, you store them in a kind of Cryo-sleep and then go visit once a month of so and talk to them. Depending on the person they can stay in this state for 15-30 years before moving on to be reborn. The other thing is that all of your items of use in your apartment need money to work. The door requires 5 cents to open, the shower a quarter. I’m not sure what the appliances buy with the money they make maybe they are saving up for something really nice.<br /><br />The issue I had with this book besides being dated is that the plot was all over the place and there really wasn’t any resolution to a lot of the threads. I was really liking the story until the halfway point when it turned into a black and white episode of the twilight zone. Then it got a bit strange but I was still following along, however the ending was completely unsatisfying overall. <br /><br />I struggled with the character development as well. Most of them were pretty flat. Even Joe Chip the main character was underdeveloped. He is an always broke guy with the ability to measure someone’s psychic potential or gift. He brings the talent to his boss who figures out how to use them in a large corporation that pretty much is a futuristic security firm of sorts. The first half of the story is centered on this and that is the part I liked more. The second half, well I mentioned the Twilight Zone so enough said there.<br /><br />Other than that there is a group of characters. The best guy friend, the love interest Joe should have had but never made the move for, the other woman that stepped in and acquired Joe for her own. Everyone else is really a throw away character. It is also so weird to read about all the smoking. Like every character in the book was a smoker and some of the story totally revolved around cigarettes. Reading it in 2018 was just strange.<br /><br />I can see how far the Sci-Fi genre has come and how PKD threw down a good base to grow off of. <b>Still it was like watching a Movie from your childhood and seeing how it just didn’t hold up over time.</b> You can still appreciate it but you’ve grown since then so it just isn’t the same.</span>
  <a data-text-id="13169047619734803775" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


